426
00:21:27.444 --> 00:21:30.544
As you know, the Cabinet Manual is the authoritative guide to central government

427
00:21:30.604 --> 00:21:34.344
decision-making in New Zealand. It derives its authority

428
00:21:34.784 --> 00:21:38.624
from its adoption by Cabinet on the publication of

429
00:21:38.664 --> 00:21:42.404
every new edition and at the beginning of each new administration.

430
00:21:42.604 --> 00:21:46.493
And we would also say that its authority also comes from

431
00:21:46.524 --> 00:21:50.444
the fact that successive administrations have adopted it or endorsed it

432
00:21:50.504 --> 00:21:54.294
as the basis on which they will operate. It's Cabinets Manual.

433
00:21:54.344 --> 00:21:57.244
It used to be called the Cabinet Office Manual back in the day, and at some point,

434
00:21:57.284 --> 00:22:00.434
the name changed. So we'll often also say it is Cabinets

435
00:22:00.524 --> 00:22:04.244
Manual. So at the beginning of each new administration, the first cabinet

436
00:22:04.284 --> 00:22:04.724
meeting

437
00:22:06.104 --> 00:22:09.504
of a new government, one of their first actions is to endorse the Cabinet Manual as

438
00:22:09.544 --> 00:22:10.964
the basis on which they'll operate.

439
00:22:11.864 --> 00:22:15.164
Obviously, there's some matters in the Cabinet Manual that reflect legislation.

440
00:22:15.264 --> 00:22:18.634
So there are parts like chapter eight, which talks about the Official Information

441
00:22:18.704 --> 00:22:21.224
Act or the Privacy Act or the Public Records Act.

442
00:22:21.324 --> 00:22:25.224
And those aspects of the manual have legislative force as well.

443
00:22:25.264 --> 00:22:29.024
But generally, the Cabinet Manual provides guidance rather than prescribing rules.

444
00:22:30.264 --> 00:22:34.134
And generally, it contains settled understandings of government practice and

445
00:22:34.184 --> 00:22:37.364
processes. And that, I think, is one of its strengths.

446
00:22:37.924 --> 00:22:41.683
It sets out the basis on which successive governments have chosen to operate,

447
00:22:42.224 --> 00:22:46.124
and we don't flip-flop backwards and forwards between with a government

448
00:22:46.204 --> 00:22:49.404
saying, "I don't like that bit, so we're not going to adopt it." So the other way

449
00:22:49.484 --> 00:22:53.404
we tend to describe it is that it tends to follow rather than

450
00:22:53.484 --> 00:22:56.624
lead change. So when we do an update,

