00:23:06.604 --> 00:23:09.974
So yeah, that's not to say the content's set in stone-

455
00:23:10.094 --> 00:23:10.094
Okay

456
00:23:10.094 --> 00:23:11.944
... but the change tends to be incremental.

457
00:23:11.984 --> 00:23:13.404
Okay.

458
00:23:13.644 --> 00:23:17.444
In terms of how the Cabinet Manual is updated, so it was first published in 1979.

459
00:23:17.944 --> 00:23:21.304
The most recent edition is the seventh, and that was published in

460
00:23:21.344 --> 00:23:22.284
2023.

461
00:23:23.444 --> 00:23:26.984
So I've been in the Cabinet Office through two updates,

462
00:23:27.484 --> 00:23:29.014
2017 and 2023.

463
00:23:30.984 --> 00:23:33.984
We undertake a review of the manual every few years,

464
00:23:34.864 --> 00:23:38.824
and the review is intended to reflect changes in procedure,

465
00:23:39.084 --> 00:23:40.884
cabinet procedure, legislation,

466
00:23:41.864 --> 00:23:44.924
administrative and constitutional arrangements, and cabinet decisions.

467
00:23:46.324 --> 00:23:49.674
There are other mechanisms for circulating and

468
00:23:49.724 --> 00:23:53.004
promulgating changes to the way a cabinet does things between

469
00:23:53.404 --> 00:23:57.134
updates of the manual. So for example, a cabinet circular might go around saying,

470
00:23:57.154 --> 00:24:01.024
"This is the position that cabinet wants you to take on Crown

471
00:24:01.084 --> 00:24:04.804
Legal matters," or those circulars will go around, and at each

472
00:24:04.864 --> 00:24:08.144
update, we will look through all the circulars and say, "Is there anything that we

473
00:24:08.164 --> 00:24:09.464
should be pulling into the manual?"

474
00:24:11.444 --> 00:24:14.664
So the way we do an update is we start by seeking the agreement of the Prime

475
00:24:14.724 --> 00:24:16.544
Minister of the day to initiate a review.

476
00:24:17.144 --> 00:24:18.744
We set up an interagency group,

477
00:24:19.744 --> 00:24:23.424
and we'll have a steering group that'll involve agencies like Crown Law, the

478
00:24:23.464 --> 00:24:25.284
central agencies, Treasury, PSC.

479
00:24:25.744 --> 00:24:27.384
There'll be a ministerial reference group

480
00:24:28.408 --> 00:24:32.168
We keep a bit of a running note of things that we think would be worth

481
00:24:32.248 --> 00:24:36.188
reviewing in future editions of the manual, and we'll put out a

482
00:24:36.228 --> 00:24:39.868
notice to all government departments, ministers, relevant agencies,

483
00:24:40.748 --> 00:24:43.748
inviting them to provide comments on the guidance in the manual and to make

484
00:24:43.788 --> 00:24:46.308
suggestions for changes that they think might be necessary.

485
00:24:47.168 --> 00:24:50.748
And then we work through that process of updating and

486
00:24:50.788 --> 00:24:54.628
finessing and checking with the ministerial reference group before we'll

487
00:24:54.668 --> 00:24:56.088
come up with a revised draft.

488
00:24:57.248 --> 00:25:01.148
And the revised final draft of that content goes to Cabinet, and it is

489
00:25:01.208 --> 00:25:03.308
agreed by Cabinet. So,

